<subSubSection id="03A9CDC4FFB7FFDC0398FAE7FAA9F8BC" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="575" pageId="1" pageNumber="574" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="4B0C9E4FFFB7FFDC0398FAE7FB00FED4" blockId="1.[151,1436,1313,2022]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1437,151,1833]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="575" pageId="1" pageNumber="574">
As two species of Leuciscidae (
<taxonomicName id="8CB3E5CCFFB7FFDF02F6FAE4FDCDFAAD" box="[505,607,1313,1337]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Alburnus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="574" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="79C7425DFFB7FFDF02F6FAE4FDCDFAAD" box="[505,607,1313,1337]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="574">Alburnus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="8CB3E5CCFFB7FFDF0161FAE4FCB7FAAD" authorityName="Bleeker" authorityYear="1860" box="[622,805,1313,1337]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Pseudophoxinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="574" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="79C7425DFFB7FFDF0161FAE4FCB7FAAD" box="[622,805,1313,1337]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="574">Pseudophoxinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) occur at Arsuz, Steindachner’s description might allow the identification of the species he had in hand. 
<bibRefCitation id="2F22E3BEFFB7FFDF01B8FA80FC09FACA" box="[695,923,1349,1374]" pageId="1" pageNumber="574" refId="ref6611" refString="Steindachner, F. (1863) Uber eine neue Alburnus - Art aus Syrien. Sitzungsberichte der Kaiserlichen Akademie der Wissenschaften. Mathematisch-Naturwissenschaftliche Classe, 48 (I Abtheilung), 193 - 194." type="journal article">Steindachner (1863)</bibRefCitation>
mentions 16 branched pectoral-fin rays in 
<taxonomicName id="8CB3E5CCFFB7FFDF068BFA83FF61FA15" authorityName="Steindachner" authorityYear="1863" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Alburnus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="574" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="kotschyi">
<emphasis id="79C7425DFFB7FFDF068BFA83FF61FA15" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="574">A. kotschyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(vs. 
<quantity id="8C4B33AAFFB7FFDF0226FAACFE19FA16" box="[297,395,1385,1410]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.064" metricValueMax="4.318" metricValueMin="3.81" pageId="1" pageNumber="574" unit="in" value="16.0" valueMax="17.0" valueMin="15.0">15–17 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName id="8CB3E5CCFFB7FFDF029EFAACFE65FA15" box="[401,503,1385,1409]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Alburnus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="574" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="79C7425DFFB7FFDF029EFAACFE65FA15" box="[401,503,1385,1409]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="574">Alburnus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Arsuz; 
<quantity id="8C4B33AAFFB7FFDF0183FAAFFD7CFA16" box="[652,750,1385,1410]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.429" metricValueMax="3.556" metricValueMin="3.302" pageId="1" pageNumber="574" unit="in" value="13.5" valueMax="14.0" valueMin="13.0">13–14 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName id="8CB3E5CCFFB7FFDF01FBFAACFC3EFA15" authorityName="Bleeker" authorityYear="1860" box="[756,940,1385,1409]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Pseudophoxinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="574" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="79C7425DFFB7FFDF01FBFAACFC3EFA15" box="[756,940,1385,1409]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="574">Pseudophoxinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Arsuz), 6 branched pelvic-fin rays (vs. 8; 7), 7½ branched anal-fin rays (vs. 9½–11½; 7½), 8½–9½ branched dorsal-fin rays (vs. 8½; 7½), 48 (total?) scales along the lateral line (vs. 49–59; 41–44), head shorter than greatest body depth (vs. longer; equal or shorter), head length about five times in total length (vs. 4.8–5.2; 4.5–4.7), head depth about 66% of head length (vs. head length 67–75%; 71–77 of head depth at nape), eye diameter 3.5 times in head length (vs. 3.3–4.0, 3.1–3.7), eye diameter less than snout length (vs. smaller; equal), eye diameter greater than interorbital distance (vs. smaller in both species), eye diameter 1.3 times in postorbital distance (vs. 
<quantity id="8C4B33AAFFB7FFDF0069F984FC44F9CE" box="[870,982,1601,1626]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.191" metricValueMax="4.572" metricValueMin="3.81" pageId="1" pageNumber="574" unit="in" value="1.65" valueMax="1.8" valueMin="1.5">1.5–1.8 in</quantity>
both species), posterior end of the upper jaw reach vertical of anterior eye margin (vs. slightly in front of vertical in both species), nares situated anteriorly to corner of mouth (vs. anterior in both species), dorsal profile slightly increasing from occiput to dorsal-fin origin (vs. slightly increasing in both species), head profile strongly decreasing from forehead to tip of snout (vs. slightly deceasing in both species), caudal peduncle depth 2.5 times in head length (vs. 2.2–2.7; 1.9–2.1); dorsal-fin origin behind vertical of pectoral-fin tip (vs. behind in both species), predorsal length about one eye diameter longer than postdorsal length (vs. predorsal length 120–140% of the sum of postdorsal length and eye diameter; 128–135%), dorsal-fin base about equal to postorbital length (vs. about equal in both species), dorsal-fin height slightly shorter than pectoral-fin length (vs. almost equal; longer), dorsal-fin height about 66% of head length (vs. 77–90%; 78– 97%), longest anal-fin ray slightly shorter than longest dorsal-fin ray (vs. shorter in both species), caudal fin deeply forked (vs. deeply forked in both species), lower caudal-fin lobe longer than head length (vs. equal; longer), largest scales slightly larger than 50% of eye diameter (vs. 57–67%; 47–60%, measured as height of lateral line scale below dorsal fin origin) and a prominent black lateral stripe (vs. present in both species). 
<bibRefCitation id="2F22E3BEFFB4FFDC0783FF52FAE2FF24" box="[1164,1392,151,176]" pageId="2" pageNumber="575" refId="ref6611" refString="Steindachner, F. (1863) Uber eine neue Alburnus - Art aus Syrien. Sitzungsberichte der Kaiserlichen Akademie der Wissenschaften. Mathematisch-Naturwissenschaftliche Classe, 48 (I Abtheilung), 193 - 194." type="journal article">Steindachner (1863)</bibRefCitation>
did not mention how he counted the last two branched rays articulating with a single pterygiophore in the anal and dorsal fins. By comparison with his text for species for which the number of branched dorsal-fin rays is not variable (7 [7½] in 
<emphasis id="79C7425DFFB4FFDC0286FEC1FD0FFE88" box="[393,669,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="575">Iberocypris alburnoides</emphasis>
, 7 [7½] in 
<taxonomicName id="8CB3E5CCFFB4FFDC003CFEC1FBB9FE88" authorityName="Iberocypris" baseAuthorityName="Steindachner" baseAuthorityYear="1866" box="[819,1067,260,284]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Anaecypris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="575" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hispanica">
<emphasis id="79C7425DFFB4FFDC003CFEC1FBB9FE88" box="[819,1067,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="575">Anaecypris hispanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 7 [7½] in 
<taxonomicName id="8CB3E5CCFFB4FFDC07CEFEC1FE61FED4" authority="(Steindachner 1866)" authorityName="Steindachner" authorityYear="1866" baseAuthorityName="Steindachner" baseAuthorityYear="1866" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Iberochondrostoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="575" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lemmingii">
<emphasis id="79C7425DFFB4FFDC07CEFEC1FE95FED4" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="575">Iberochondrostoma lemmingii</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="2F22E3BEFFB4FFDC021AFEE2FE7EFED4" box="[277,492,295,320]" pageId="2" pageNumber="575" refId="ref6647" refString="Steindachner, F. (1866) Allgemeine Bemerkungen uber die Susswasserfische Spaniens und Portugals und Revision der einzelnen Arten. Selbstverlag des Verfassers, Wien, 15 pp." type="book">Steindachner 1866</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, we deduce that he counted the last two rays as a single ray.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4B0C9E4FFFB4FFDC03C8FE89FD01FC14" blockId="2.[151,1437,151,1833]" pageId="2" pageNumber="575">
While the 
<taxonomicName id="8CB3E5CCFFB4FFDC0233FE89FE61FEF0" authorityName="Bleeker" authorityYear="1860" box="[316,499,332,356]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Pseudophoxinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="575" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="79C7425DFFB4FFDC0233FE89FE61FEF0" box="[316,499,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="575">Pseudophoxinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Arsuz agrees with the description of 
<taxonomicName id="8CB3E5CCFFB4FFDC00DBFE89FBDDFEF0" authorityName="Steindachner" authorityYear="1863" box="[980,1103,332,356]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Alburnus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="575" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="kotschyi">
<emphasis id="79C7425DFFB4FFDC00DBFE89FBDDFEF0" box="[980,1103,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="575">A. kotschyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having 7½ branched analfin rays and some of the characters mentioned above, it is also distinct by having, among other characters, 7½ branched dorsal-fin rays (vs. 8½–9½), and 41–44 total lateral-line scales (vs. 48). The 
<taxonomicName id="8CB3E5CCFFB4FFDC0770FE51FB74FE38" box="[1151,1254,404,428]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Alburnus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="575" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="79C7425DFFB4FFDC0770FE51FB74FE38" box="[1151,1254,404,428]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="575">Alburnus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
found in Arsuz agrees with Steindachner’s description by having 8½ branched dorsal-fin rays, being superficially very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="8CB3E5CCFFB4FFDC0398FE19FEB4FE60" baseAuthorityName="Bonaparte" baseAuthorityYear="1841" box="[151,294,476,500]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Alburnus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="575" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="arborella">
<emphasis id="79C7425DFFB4FFDC0398FE19FEB4FE60" box="[151,294,476,500]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="575">A. arborella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but it differs from the description by having 51–58 total lateral-line scales (vs. 48, 49– 
<quantity id="8C4B33AAFFB4FFDC0652FE19FA0EFE61" box="[1373,1436,476,501]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4986" pageId="2" pageNumber="575" unit="in" value="59.0">59 in</quantity>
populations from Seyhan and Ceyhan), 9½–10½ branched anal-fin rays (vs. 7½) and some characters mentioned above. We exclude the possibility that 
<bibRefCitation id="2F22E3BEFFB4FFDC018FFDE1FCFEFDA9" box="[640,876,548,573]" pageId="2" pageNumber="575" refId="ref6611" refString="Steindachner, F. (1863) Uber eine neue Alburnus - Art aus Syrien. Sitzungsberichte der Kaiserlichen Akademie der Wissenschaften. Mathematisch-Naturwissenschaftliche Classe, 48 (I Abtheilung), 193 - 194." type="journal article">Steindachner (1863)</bibRefCitation>
had seen hybrids between the 
<taxonomicName id="8CB3E5CCFFB4FFDC07F3FDE1FAF0FDA8" box="[1276,1378,548,572]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Alburnus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="575" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="79C7425DFFB4FFDC07F3FDE1FAF0FDA8" box="[1276,1378,548,572]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="575">Alburnus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="8CB3E5CCFFB4FFDC0398FD8DFEDDFDF4" authorityName="Bleeker" authorityYear="1860" box="[151,335,584,608]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Pseudophoxinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="575" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="79C7425DFFB4FFDC0398FD8DFEDDFDF4" box="[151,335,584,608]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="575">Pseudophoxinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as such hybrids should be intermediate between parents at least in meristic characters, and this is not the case in the characters given in the description by Steindachner. We cannot exclude the possibility that an additional species was present in Arsuz in Steindachner’s time, which is now extinct, extirpated or could simply not be collected by us. The fact, that 
<bibRefCitation id="2F22E3BEFFB4FFDC011AFD71FD68FD59" box="[533,762,692,717]" pageId="2" pageNumber="575" refId="ref6611" refString="Steindachner, F. (1863) Uber eine neue Alburnus - Art aus Syrien. Sitzungsberichte der Kaiserlichen Akademie der Wissenschaften. Mathematisch-Naturwissenschaftliche Classe, 48 (I Abtheilung), 193 - 194." type="journal article">Steindachner (1863)</bibRefCitation>
stated that the fishes are of 
<quantity id="8C4B33AAFFB4FFDC0730FD71FB5AFD58" box="[1087,1224,692,717]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="575" unit="mm" value="75.0" valueMax="100.0" valueMin="50.0">50–100 mm</quantity>
(most likely) total length makes clear that he had more than one individual in hand. We could also not exclude that 
<bibRefCitation id="2F22E3BEFFB4FFDC0604FD12FF73FC81" pageId="2" pageNumber="575" refId="ref6611" refString="Steindachner, F. (1863) Uber eine neue Alburnus - Art aus Syrien. Sitzungsberichte der Kaiserlichen Akademie der Wissenschaften. Mathematisch-Naturwissenschaftliche Classe, 48 (I Abtheilung), 193 - 194." type="journal article">Steindachner (1863)</bibRefCitation>
had mixed the 
<taxonomicName id="8CB3E5CCFFB4FFDC0280FD39FDD4FC80" authorityName="Bleeker" authorityYear="1860" box="[399,582,764,788]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Pseudophoxinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="575" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="79C7425DFFB4FFDC0280FD39FDD4FC80" box="[399,582,764,788]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="575">Pseudophoxinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the 
<taxonomicName id="8CB3E5CCFFB4FFDC01A8FD39FC9CFC80" box="[679,782,764,788]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Alburnus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="575" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="79C7425DFFB4FFDC01A8FD39FC9CFC80" box="[679,782,764,788]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="575">Alburnus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Arsuz in his description. However, no variations are given in the description, which suggests it was based on a single individual only. No other leuciscid known from adjacent areas fully agrees with Steindachner’s description, so only an extinct species or a species not yet discovered could be taken into consideration.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4B0C9E4FFFB4FFDC03C8FC49FAA5FB50" blockId="2.[151,1437,151,1833]" pageId="2" pageNumber="575">
Therefore, we find here clearly the situation where a name cannot be connected to a species without uncertainties. To eliminate these uncertainties concerning the application of the name 
<taxonomicName id="8CB3E5CCFFB4FFDC0771FC75FB6FFC5C" authorityName="Steindachner" authorityYear="1863" box="[1150,1277,944,968]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Alburnus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="575" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="kotschyi">
<emphasis id="79C7425DFFB4FFDC0771FC75FB6FFC5C" box="[1150,1277,944,968]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="575">A. kotschyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and potential confusion with any known species we designate here one individual of 
<taxonomicName id="8CB3E5CCFFB4FFDC00C1FC11FBA6FC78" box="[974,1076,980,1004]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Alburnus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="575" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="79C7425DFFB4FFDC00C1FC11FBA6FC78" box="[974,1076,980,1004]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="575">Alburnus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
collected from Arsuz (
<collectionCode id="2DA2068AFFB4FFDC064FFC11FA0EFC78" box="[1344,1436,980,1004]" pageId="2" pageNumber="575">IUSHM</collectionCode>
37900-253, 
<figureCitation id="D38882CAFFB4FFDC022DFC32FEF4FB84" box="[290,358,1015,1040]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,249,1909,1931]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,985,1888]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,985,1888]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1.Alburnus kotschyi, IUSHM 37900-253, neotype, 79.2 mm SL; Turkey: Arsuz." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1182984/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="575">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
) as 
<typeStatus id="940820EDFFB4FFDC0290FC3DFE6AFB84" box="[415,504,1016,1040]" pageId="2" pageNumber="575">neotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="8CB3E5CCFFB4FFDC012AFC3DFD36FB84" authorityName="Steindachner" authorityYear="1863" box="[549,676,1016,1040]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Alburnus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="575" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="kotschyi">
<emphasis id="79C7425DFFB4FFDC012AFC3DFD36FB84" box="[549,676,1016,1040]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="575">A. kotschyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This species is superficially similar to 
<taxonomicName id="8CB3E5CCFFB4FFDC0771FC3DFA99FB84" baseAuthorityName="Bonaparte" baseAuthorityYear="1841" box="[1150,1291,1016,1040]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Alburnus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="575" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="arborella">
<emphasis id="79C7425DFFB4FFDC0771FC3DFA99FB84" box="[1150,1291,1016,1040]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="575">A. arborella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and has the distinguishing character states of 
<taxonomicName id="8CB3E5CCFFB4FFDC0112FBD9FCE4FBA1" authority="sensu Steindacher" authorityName="Steindacher" box="[541,886,1052,1077]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Alburnus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="575" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="kotschyi">
<emphasis id="79C7425DFFB4FFDC0112FBD9FD0EFBA0" box="[541,668,1052,1076]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="575">A. kotschyi</emphasis>
sensu Steindacher
</taxonomicName>
, viz. 8½ branched dorsal fin rays, a prominent lateral stripe, head length 5 times in total length and predorsal length about one eye diameter longer than postdorsal length (see others above). As the name 
<taxonomicName id="8CB3E5CCFFB4FFDC016DFBA1FD4DFBE8" box="[610,735,1124,1148]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Alburnus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="575" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="kotschyi">
<emphasis id="79C7425DFFB4FFDC016DFBA1FD4DFBE8" box="[610,735,1124,1148]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="575">A. kotschyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has already been used by several authors (
<bibRefCitation id="2F22E3BEFFB4FFDC07C0FBA1FA0AFBE8" box="[1231,1432,1124,1148]" pageId="2" pageNumber="575" refId="ref6454" refString="Perea, S., Bohme, M., Zupancic, P., Freyhof, J., Sanda, R., Ozulug, M., Abdoli, A. &amp; Doadrio, I. (2010) Phylogenetic relationships and biogeographical patterns in Circum-Mediterranean subfamily Leuciscinae (Teleostei, Cyprinidae) inferred from both mitochondrial and nuclear data. BMC Evolutionary Biology, 10, 265. https: // doi. org / 10.1186 / 1471 - 2148 - 10 - 265" type="journal article">
Perea 
<emphasis id="79C7425DFFB4FFDC0616FBA0FAC6FBE8" box="[1305,1364,1124,1148]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="575">et al.</emphasis>
2010
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="2F22E3BEFFB4FFDC0398FB42FEF4FB34" box="[151,358,1159,1184]" pageId="2" pageNumber="575" refId="ref6139" refString="Geiger, M. F., Herder, F., Monaghan, M. T., Almada, V., Barbieri, R., Bariche, M., Berrebi, P., Bohlen, J., Casal-Lopez, M., Delmastro, G. B., Denys, G. P. J., Dettai, A., Doadrio, I., Kalogianni, E., Karst, H., Kottelat, M., Kovacic, M., Laporte, M., Lorenzoni, M., Marcic, Z., Ozulug, M., Perdices, A., Perea, S., Persat, H., Porcelotti, S., Puzzi, C., Robalo, J., Sanda, R., Schneider, M., Slechtova, V., Stoumboudi, M., Walter, S. &amp; Freyhof, J. (2014) Spatial heterogeneity in the Mediterranean Biodiversity Hotspot affects barcoding accuracy of its freshwater fishes. Molecular Ecology Resources, 14, 1210 - 1221. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / 1755 - 0998.12257" type="journal article">
Geiger 
<emphasis id="79C7425DFFB4FFDC03E5FB4CFE8EFB34" box="[234,284,1160,1184]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="575">et al</emphasis>
. 2014
</bibRefCitation>
), the 
<typeStatus id="940820EDFFB4FFDC02ACFB4CFE6EFB35" box="[419,508,1161,1185]" pageId="2" pageNumber="575">neotype</typeStatus>
designation stabilizes the use of the name 
<taxonomicName id="8CB3E5CCFFB4FFDC00D3FB4DFBCAFB34" box="[988,1112,1160,1184]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Alburnus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="575" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="kotschyi">
<emphasis id="79C7425DFFB4FFDC00D3FB4DFBCAFB34" box="[988,1112,1160,1184]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="575">A. kotschyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
rather than destabilizes it by transferring it to a species of 
<taxonomicName id="8CB3E5CCFFB4FFDC02D2FB69FD06FB50" authorityName="Bleeker" authorityYear="1860" box="[477,660,1196,1220]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Pseudophoxinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="575" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="79C7425DFFB4FFDC02D2FB69FD06FB50" box="[477,660,1196,1220]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="575">Pseudophoxinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which is only indicated by the branched anal-fin ray count.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4B0C9E4FFFB4FFDC03C8FB15FAADF8BC" blockId="2.[151,1437,151,1833]" pageId="2" pageNumber="575">
<bibRefCitation id="2F22E3BEFFB4FFDC03C8FB15FE46FB7C" box="[199,468,1231,1256]" pageId="2" pageNumber="575" refId="ref6353" refString="ICZN (International Code of Zoological Nomenclature) (1999) International Code of Zoological Nomenclature. 4 th Edition. International Trust for Zoological Nomenlature, London, 306 pp." type="book">
<collectionCode id="2DA2068AFFB4FFDC03C8FB15FE9AFB7C" box="[199,264,1232,1256]" pageId="2" pageNumber="575">ICZN</collectionCode>
(1999: Art. 75.3)
</bibRefCitation>
prescribes seven qualifying conditions to designate a 
<typeStatus id="940820EDFFB4FFDC074DFB14FB0CFB7D" box="[1090,1182,1233,1257]" pageId="2" pageNumber="575">neotype</typeStatus>
. Art. 75.3.1. require a statement that the 
<typeStatus id="940820EDFFB4FFDC0268FB30FE52FA99" box="[359,448,1269,1293]" pageId="2" pageNumber="575">neotype</typeStatus>
is designated with the express purpose of clarifying the taxonomic status of a nominal taxon. As 
<taxonomicName id="8CB3E5CCFFB4FFDC0205FADDFE17FAA4" box="[266,389,1304,1328]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Alburnus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="575" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="kotschyi">
<emphasis id="79C7425DFFB4FFDC0205FADDFE17FAA4" box="[266,389,1304,1328]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="575">A. kotschyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
cannot be identified from the description, no 
<typeStatus id="940820EDFFB4FFDC0085FADCFC28FAA5" box="[906,954,1305,1329]" pageId="2" pageNumber="575">type</typeStatus>
is left and two similar species occur at the 
<typeStatus id="940820EDFFB4FFDC0398FAF8FF55FAC1" box="[151,199,1341,1365]" pageId="2" pageNumber="575">type</typeStatus>
locality, only a 
<typeStatus id="940820EDFFB4FFDC0281FAF8FE75FAC1" box="[398,487,1341,1365]" pageId="2" pageNumber="575">neotype</typeStatus>
designation clarifies the taxonomic status of the species. Art. 75.3.2. requires a statement of the characters that the author regards as differentiating the species from its congeners. The diagnosis given below satisfies this requirement. Art. 75.3.3. requires data and description sufficient to ensure recognition of the specimen designated. The diagnosis and description given below satisfies this requirement. Art. 75.3.4. requires that the author's reasons for believing the name-bearing 
<typeStatus id="940820EDFFB4FFDC0004FA08FCA9FA71" box="[779,827,1485,1509]" pageId="2" pageNumber="575">type</typeStatus>
specimen(s) to be lost or destroyed be stated, together with the steps taken to trace it or them. No 
<typeStatus id="940820EDFFB4FFDC0172FA34FD3FF99D" box="[637,685,1521,1545]" pageId="2" pageNumber="575">type</typeStatus>
material was found in the Steindachner collection at 
<collectionCode id="2DA2068AFFB4FFDC060BFA34FADEF99C" box="[1284,1356,1521,1544]" country="Austria" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/c7yt-hh77" name="Naturhistorisches Museum, Wien" pageId="2" pageNumber="575">NMW</collectionCode>
, which is the only repository known to contain his fish specimens (H. Wellendorf, 
<collectionCode id="2DA2068AFFB4FFDC00D3F9D0FBB6F9B8" box="[988,1060,1557,1580]" country="Austria" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/c7yt-hh77" name="Naturhistorisches Museum, Wien" pageId="2" pageNumber="575">NMW</collectionCode>
, pers. comm., 
<date id="3F0DB88FFFB4FFDC07C9F9D1FACCF9B8" box="[1222,1374,1556,1580]" pageId="2" pageNumber="575" value="2008-09-23">23 Sept 2008</date>
). Art. 75.3.5. requires evidence that the 
<typeStatus id="940820EDFFB4FFDC011CF9FCFDFEF9C5" box="[531,620,1593,1617]" pageId="2" pageNumber="575">neotype</typeStatus>
be consistent with what is known of the former name-bearing 
<typeStatus id="940820EDFFB4FFDC0621F9FCFACCF9C5" box="[1326,1374,1593,1617]" pageId="2" pageNumber="575">type</typeStatus>
from the original description. Some of the most important diagnostic characters of the species (see above) are visible in the 
<typeStatus id="940820EDFFB4FFDC03CFF944FE8EF90D" box="[192,284,1665,1689]" pageId="2" pageNumber="575">neotype</typeStatus>
. Art. 75.3.6. requires that the 
<typeStatus id="940820EDFFB4FFDC0166F944FD50F90D" box="[617,706,1665,1689]" pageId="2" pageNumber="575">neotype</typeStatus>
comes from a location as close as practicable to the original 
<typeStatus id="940820EDFFB4FFDC0663F944FA0EF90D" box="[1388,1436,1665,1689]" pageId="2" pageNumber="575">type</typeStatus>
locality, meaning from Arsuz, which it does. We see no reason to believe, that Steindachner's Arsus is different from the today city of Arzus. Art. 75.3.7. requires a statement that the 
<typeStatus id="940820EDFFB4FFDC00DBF90CFBBFF975" box="[980,1069,1737,1761]" pageId="2" pageNumber="575">neotype</typeStatus>
is the property of a recognized scientific or educational institution, cited by name, that maintains a research collection, with proper facilities for preserving name-bearing 
<typeStatus id="940820EDFFB4FFDC02BAF8D4FE61F8BD" box="[437,499,1809,1833]" pageId="2" pageNumber="575">types</typeStatus>
, and that makes them accessible for study. 
<collectionCode id="2DA2068AFFB4FFDC00DAF8D5FBBDF8BC" box="[981,1071,1808,1832]" pageId="2" pageNumber="575">IUSHM</collectionCode>
fulfils this requirement.
</paragraph>
